- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the hardness of obtaining small solutions, which is a common topic in algorithmic research. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with omega-automata and regular languages. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper may have implications for programming language design and verification. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also possible as the paper discusses winning strategies in games with omega-regular winning conditions.
